<body>
    <h1>Manual Installation on Windows</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-Preparation:">Preparation:</h=
2>
<h3 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-1.SetupPHP">1. Set up PHP</h3>
<p>This step requires the modification of two files: Apache2 configuration =
file and&nbsp;<code>php.ini</code>.<br>These files can be edited using a te=
rminal editor like vi or nano, or a simple text editor. file name is <stron=
g>httpd.conf&nbsp;</strong>and by default it is located in this directory:<=
/p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\Apache2.2\conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>a. Uncomment the following line:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">LoadModule php5_module libexec/apache2/libphp5.so</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>b. Locate php.ini file. By default it should be in the following directo=
ry:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">C:\program files\php\php.ini</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>c. Open the file in a text editor and locate&nbsp;<code>date.timezone</c=
ode>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code>pdo_mysql.default_socket</code>&nbsp;and provide t=
hem with values as in the example below:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">date.timezone =3D "Europe/Warsaw"
pdo_mysql.default_socket =3D /tmp/mysql.sock</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>d. Increase&nbsp;<code>memory_limit</code>&nbsp;value for eZ Platform:</=
p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">memory_limit =3D 4G</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-2.SetupvirtualhostandstartApache2">2.=
 Set up virtual host and start Apache2</h3>
<p>a. Edit Apache2 configuration file:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">c:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\Apache2.2\conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>b. Uncomment and modify the following lines:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">LoadModule vhost_alias_module libexec/apache2/mod_vhost_alias.so
LoadModule rewrite_module libexec/apache2/mod_rewrite.so</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>c. Comment the following line:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">Include /private/etc/apache2/extra/httpd-vhosts.conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>d. Add the following line to the file:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">Include /private/etc/apache2/users/*.conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-3.StartApache2daemonusingCommandLine"=
>3. Start Apache2 daemon using Command Line</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">httpd.exe</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-4.InstallComposerglobally">4. Install=
 Composer globally</h3>
<p>Composer is a dependency manager that allows you to install packages dir=
ectly in the project. It is also checking all packages' versions on a regul=
ar basis to make sure they are up-to-date and to avoid inconsistencies.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">curl -sS&nbsp;https://getcomposer.org/installer&nbsp;| php
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-5.CreateanewdatabaseforeZPlatform">5.=
 Create a new database for eZ Platform</h3>
<p>Create new database (you can substitute&nbsp;<code>ez1</code>&nbsp;with =
the database name you want to use):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">mysql -uroot -ppassword -e "CREATE DATABASE ez1"</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-6.InstalladditionalrequirementsforeZP=
latform">6. Install additional requirements for eZ Platform</h3>
<p>a. Install PEAR/PECL extension:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">cd c:\program files\php\php.ini
curl -O https://pear.php.net/go-pear.phar
php -d detect_unicode=3D0 go-pear.phar
php install-pear-nozlib.phar
pear channel-update pear.php.net
pecl channel-update pecl.php.net
pear upgrade-all
pear config-set auto_discover 1</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>b. Edit&nbsp;<code>php.ini</code>&nbsp;and add following line:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">extension=3Dintl.so</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>c. Enable opcache extension for PHP (suggested, but not required) by add=
ing:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">zend_extension=3Dopcache.so</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-Installation:">Installation:</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ManualInstallationonWindows-7.InstalleZPlatform"><br>7. Install e=
Z Platform</h3>
<p>a.&nbsp;Download archive from&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/downloa=
ds/downloads" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">share.ez.no/download=
s</a>.&nbsp;Extract the eZ Platform&nbsp;archive to a directory, then execu=
te post install scripts.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">cd /&lt;directory&gt;/
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar run-script post-install-cmd</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>b. Copy the virtual host template:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">COPY c:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\Apache2.2\vhost.t=
emplate c:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\Apache2.2\users/ez1.lh.=
conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>d. Modify virtual host file&nbsp;<strong>vhost.template.&nbsp;</strong><=
/p>
<p>Replace the&nbsp;<code>---USER_ID---</code>&nbsp;variable (used in lines=
 10 and 17) with your current user ID. Use&nbsp;<code>whoami</code>&nbsp;co=
mmand to get effective user ID of the currently logged user. If you want to=
 use the default virtual host template (delivered with eZ Platform package)=
 all you have to do is set up lines 7, 8, 9, 10, 17, 25 and 33:</p>
<p>e. Restart Apache 2 server:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">httpd.exe -k restart</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>f. Install required dependencies using Composer:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">composer install</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>When Composer asks you for the token you must log in to your GitHub acco=
unt and edit your profile. Go to the Personal access tokens link and Genera=
te new token with default settings. Be aware that the token will be shown o=
nly once, so do not refresh the page until you paste the token into Compose=
r prompt. This operation is performed only once when you install eZ Platfor=
m for the first time.</p>
<p>h. Install eZ Platform:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php app/console ezplatform:install clean</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><br>You will be able to see your page under&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://ez1.l=
h" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://ez1.lh</a>&nbsp;(or the =
address you chose in preparation). Please note that a clean install of eZ P=
latform doesn=E2=80=99t include DemoBundle anymore.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
